######## CSCI 662 Homework 2 - Viterbi Noisy Channel Decoder System ##########
######## Niki Parmar - USC ID 8436806920 #####################################
##############################################################################

Methodology :
Implement the Viterbi algorithm to tag English sentences with appropiate Part Of Speech tags
using the Noisy Channel Model.
Use the naive add 1 smoothing method to consider the unseen tag sequences and unseen word to tag sequences.
Take log values of probabilities to prevent underflow.

Input: 

training-data
Set of English Sentences with given tag sequences.

test-data
Set of English sentences to be tagged

Output: 

Tagged sentences
A single tag for each word in each sentence.

To run the program use the following command:

python viterbi-decoder.py training-data test-data > tagged-data
